{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45331].
  {panel}

h4. Current Behaviour

We can search for a page title and it will show in the search results (in the macro). Or we can use {{SPACEKEY:Page name}} matching the exact name to find it. There is no search results in the last case.

 
h4. Use Case

Similar to finding a page with excerpt include macro, provide the search functionality to be able to find pages from a certain space without having to match: {{SPACEKEY:Page name exactly.}}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45323].
  {panel}

My team relies heavily on feature specific JIRA filters on our confluence page. They are an amazing way for us to see the remaining ticket in a project.

The one thing that is missing is the ability to show a total for the time fields (or story points if you use those). Our PMs end up copying the data into a spread sheet or using a sum equation in a JIRA search so that they can see the total remaining time.

It would be very helpful to be able to see a total at the bottom.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45307].
  {panel}

I am wanting to know if its possible to have a better install system for confluence or a better way to make changes for example when confluence install, for people to access the site they have to use a port number. Would be great if in the admin section of confluence if people would like to run confluence on say confluence.domain.com instead of domain.com:9080 would be easier for a gui based type instead of doing it all command line.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45306].
  {panel}

Hi

I would like to make a suggestion to see if its possible to make it easier to install a SSL Certificate. I am not the great with Command Line and linux and don't really understand how to install an SSL Certificate  and I think it would be better if  you had a GUI Based System in the admin area of Confluence that allowed users to request a csr and also install a ssl certificate without having to do command line if people don't want to

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45303].
  {panel}

We create a space for each client and have standard page names in each one, eg Logins. 

The dashboard listings provided, Recent activity, only include the page name and not the Space name. Makes them worse than useless for us. Please add an option to include space name wherever page names are listed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45299].
  {panel}

As of now we don't have a function in our REST API document that will help to retrieve this data. It would be great if we can have this.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45288].
  {panel}

Please provide a way for Confluence Cloud users to automatically schedule backups, so we have a permanent copy of our data in case of accidental deletions or other losses.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45287].
  {panel}

I had the unfortunate experience of deleting a Space I thought was empty, but apparently contained Restricted pages that were not visible to me.

The permissions should be more consistent, so that I don't have authority to delete pages I don't have permission to see.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45286].
  {panel}

Currently, there is a top-level tab under Overview for Deleting a Space, while Archiving is a buried option. It should be easy to find the (reversible) Archive option, but difficult to find the (permanent) Deletion.

