h3.Workaround
This is often caused by there being two spaces in a single space export file. The workaround is to import the export file into a Confluence Server instance, then re-export just the one single space you're trying to import in the first place.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45273].
  {panel}

The idea is that we will assume that the proxy is started successfully, then we will do the health check for the proxy and log out any errors found.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45272].
  {panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45252].
  {panel}

There are REST APIs for creating and publishing shared drafts, but not for editing shared draft. Would be nice to have also REST API for updating/editing shared drafts without publishing.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45248].
  {panel}

https://pug.jira-dev.com/wiki/spaces/COLLAB/pages/2362769417/How+to+disable+grammarly+extension+for+quick+editor+more+gently

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45235].
  {panel}

For some reason, Synchrony will make a request to itself, using the base URL that is specified in Confluence.

In some scenarios, customers choose to use port forwarding via IP tables (or the like) that makes this scenario a little trickier to setup. For example, a customer may choose to forward 80 » 8090, and 443 » 8443.

If the local machine doesn't have access to itself over port 80 (or 443) then the connection will fail:
{code:java}
org.apache.http.conn.HttpHostConnectException: Connect to base.url:443 [base.url/127.0.0.1, base.url/0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1] failed: Connection refused

{code}
If possible, this port should be configurable to make it easier for Synchrony to slot in with existing systems.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45224].
  {panel}

*Summary*


User like to have panel macro with Transparent images.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45211].
  {panel}

It would be nice to have a feature in confluence where information that is not updated in a certain amount of time is automatically deleted. While researching whether this feature was available, I ran across several instances of users asking for the same thing. Thanks so much!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45205].
  {panel}

Currently I have many users who would like to see the "creator" of a task in the "task report"

I can modify the column in the macro but unfortunately the "creator" does not add..

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45200].
  {panel}

As per https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-37623, images cannot be attached to global templates. They also cannot be dragged in.

However, images can be pasted in, which will work fine until you attempt to save. When you attempt to save after pasting an image in, the save will fail for no reason and with no feedback to the user.

Confluence should either warn images aren't able to be pasted in, adjust the image so it references the page / URL it came from or strip the image out.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45194].
  {panel}

With our Confluence users linking to LDAP, it is difficult having to create and delete groups to control permissions.


 Whilst it is great having permission controls for each space, this can be a nightmare going through each one to control individual users and having a list the length of my arm to constantly monitor this. We don't want all users having the ability to create, modify and view every page. It would be great if you can view the *users profile* within *User Management* to control what spaces they can and can't access and edit (As shown below).


 Please consider this suggestion.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-45185].
  {panel}

